            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Keep in mind `jobsend()` is for sending input to a job (and terminal buffers are jobs). Currently there's no way to attach a stdout handler to a job after it's already been created (which is the case for `:term`), but you can create a terminal job with `termopen()` (takes the same arguments as `jobstart()`).\r\n\r\n>  it'll be possible in the future to do the following:\r\n\r\nYes. ",
